* Zaghloul ( ) – Dark red skin , long , and very crunchy when fresh ( when they are typically served ) ; extremely sweet , with sugar content creating a sense of desiccation in the mouth when eaten .
The variety is essentially exclusive to Egypt , where it is subject to an element of nationalist sentiment on account of sharing a name with national hero Saad Zaghloul .
